 Non-limiting examples of therapeutic agents for multiple sclerosis with which an antibody, or antibody portion, of the invention can be combined include the following : corticosteroids ; prednisolone ; methylprednisolone ; azathioprine ; cyclophosphamide ; cyclosporine ; methotrexate ; 4-aminopyridine ; tizanidine ; interferon- (31 a (Avonex ;
Biogen) ; interferon-sslb (Betaseron ; Chiron/Berlex) ; Copolymer 1 (Cop-1 ; Copaxone ;
Teva Pharmaceutical Industries, Inc.) ; hyperbaric oxygen ; intravenous immunoglobulin ; clabribine ; antibodies to or antagonists of other human cytokines or growth factors, for example, TNF, LT, IL-1, IL-2, IL-6, IL-7, IL-8, IL-12, IL-15, IL-16, EMAP-11, GM
CSF, FGF, and PDGF. Antibodies of the invention, or antigen binding portions thereof, can be combined with antibodies to cell surface molecules such as CD2, CD3, CD4, CD8, CD25, CD28, CD30, CD40, CD45, CD69, CD80, CD86, CD90 or their ligands.

